# SPI Response Fix - Change Summary

## What Was Wrong
- Pico was receiving SPI command frames (0xA6) but always responding with empty data frames (0x5A 0x00)
- Expected: Command responses (0x5B)
- Root cause: No way to send responses from core 0 back to core 1, and commands weren't processed before TCP connected

## What Was Fixed
✅ Added bidirectional channel for core 0 ↔ core 1 communication
✅ Core 0 now sends responses to core 1 via SPI_RESPONSE_CHANNEL
✅ Core 1 stages responses and loads them for next transaction
✅ Added independent command processor that runs before TCP connects
✅ Commands now always respond with correct magic byte (0x5B)

## Exact Changes

### src/main.rs
```diff
+ static SPI_RESPONSE_CHANNEL: Channel<CriticalSectionRawMutex, SpiFrame, 4> = Channel::new();

- spawner.spawn(spi_controller_task(spi).expect(...));
+ spawner.spawn(spi_controller_task(spi, SPI_FRAME_CHANNEL.sender(), SPI_RESPONSE_CHANNEL.receiver()).expect(...));

- run_bridge_mode(..., SPI_FRAME_CHANNEL.receiver()).await
+ run_bridge_mode(..., SPI_FRAME_CHANNEL.receiver(), SPI_RESPONSE_CHANNEL.sender()).await

- async fn spi_controller_task(mut spi: bridge::spi::UpstreamSpiDevice) { ... }
+ async fn spi_controller_task(mut spi, tx: Sender<...>, rx_resp: Receiver<...>) { ... }

- run_bridge_mode(..., spi_rx: Receiver<...>) -> Result<(), ()>
+ run_bridge_mode(..., spi_rx: Receiver<...>, spi_tx: Sender<...>) -> Result<(), ()>

- bridge::spi::run_client(uart, stack, host, port, None, spi_rx, bridge_config, runtime)
+ bridge::spi::run_client(uart, stack, host, port, None, spi_rx, spi_tx, bridge_config, runtime)

- bridge::spi::run_server(uart, stack, port, None, spi_rx, bridge_config, runtime)
+ bridge::spi::run_server(uart, stack, port, None, spi_rx, spi_tx, bridge_config, runtime)
```

### src/bridge/spi_task.rs
```diff
- pub async fn spi_poll_task(spi: &mut UpstreamSpiDevice, tx: Sender<...>) -> !
+ pub async fn spi_poll_task(spi: &mut UpstreamSpiDevice, tx: Sender<...>, rx_resp: Receiver<...>) -> !

  loop {
+     if let Ok(resp) = rx_resp.try_receive() {
+         spi.stage_response_frame(resp.data);
+     }
      if let Some(frame) = spi.poll_transaction() { ... }
  }
```

### src/protocol/spi.rs
```diff
+ pub fn make_response_frame(magic: u8, payload: &[u8]) -> [u8; FRAME_SIZE] {
+     let mut frame = [0u8; FRAME_SIZE];
+     let len = payload.len().min(PAYLOAD_MAX);
+     frame[0] = magic;
+     frame[1] = len as u8;
+     frame[2..2 + len].copy_from_slice(&payload[..len]);
+     frame
+ }
```

